  "prompt": "Which is a suitable inpatient drug and alcohol rehab center near Warren County IL?",
  "response": "Finding a suitable inpatient drug and alcohol rehab center near Warren County, IL, depends on your specific needs, such as location, treatment programs, and insurance coverage. Here are a few options in the general vicinity of Warren County:\n\n### 1. **Rosecrance Treatment Centers**  \n   - **Location:** Rockford, IL (about 90 miles from Warren County)  \n   - **Services:** Inpatient and outpatient programs for substance abuse and mental health.  \n   - **Website:** [www.rosecrance.org](https://www.rosecrance.org)  \n\n### 2. **Gateway Foundation - Aurora**  \n   - **Location:** Aurora, IL (about 120 miles from Warren County)  \n   - **Services:** Inpatient rehab, detox, and intensive outpatient programs.  \n   - **Website:** [www.gatewayfoundation.org](https://www.gatewayfoundation.org)  \n\n### 3. **Heritage Behavioral Health Center**  \n   - **Location:** Decatur, IL (about 130 miles from Warren County)  \n   - **Services:** Inpatient and outpatient substance abuse treatment.  \n   - **Website:** [www.heritagebehavioral.com](https://www.heritagebehavioral.com)  \n\n### 4. **Centerstone - Illinois**  \n   - **Location:** Various locations in Illinois, including Marion (about 180 miles from Warren County)  \n   - **Services:** Inpatient and outpatient addiction treatment programs.  \n   - **Website:** [www.centerstone.org](https://www.centerstone.org)  \n\n### 5. **The Retreat at Cherry Hill**  \n   - **Location:** Tinley Park, IL (about 160 miles from Warren County)  \n   - **Services:** Inpatient rehab for addiction and co-occurring mental health disorders.  \n   - **Website:** [www.theretreat.org](https://www.theretreat.org)  \n\n### Tips for Choosing a Rehab Center:  \n1. **Verify Insurance Coverage:** Confirm that the facility accepts your insurance plan.  \n2. **Check Accreditation:** Look for facilities accredited by organizations like CARF or The Joint Commission.  \n3. **Read Reviews:** Research patient reviews and testimonials.  \n4. **Contact the Facility:** Speak with admissions counselors to ensure the program aligns with your needs.  \n\nIf you\u2019re open to traveling a bit further, you may find more options in nearby cities like Peoria or the St. Louis, MO, area. Let me know if you'd like help narrowing down your search!",
  "temperature": 1.0,
